First visit to the Iowa Chop House will not be the last. The welcoming and casual atmosphere felt relaxing and unassuming but they have a claim to braggadocio as the menu selections, food quality, and presentation are second to none. Our friendly server, Eli, was knowledgeable and guided us well along our journey. He offered excellent descriptions and justified suggestions to help our party have the best possible dining experience. The cold, crisp wedge salad was a nice start to the meal, along side the hand battered Frickle spears and the full pound of maple glazed thick cut bacon appetizers. Our entrees ran the gamut from the Chop House Mac & Cheese (topped with bacon and fried onion strings), a juicy and thick bone-in pork chop to monstrous 24oz porterhouse steak. Local sourcing helps keep the quality up and the kitchen did an expert job preparing our meal. The side dishes were presented in small wire baskets and little iron pots and stainless steel pans. Very well played, IHC. Though we were well fed, we shared a table side torched creme brulee. The mixologists talent showed through in the cocktail menu but the real gem is the Beer Barn. Taste all of Iowa's best draft beers all in one spot. I highly recommend Iowa Chop House as a destination to dine in this friendly college town. Cheers!

I do not use that site but still downloaded their app to confirm and they still called me hours later to confirm again. Burgers and sandwiches are fine, fries too. Mac&cheese looks interesting with the skillet and crumbs on top but then it is just like kraft or velveeta. Even our kids, who love pasta with anything, disliked this. The beef appetizer is worth trying, full of flavor! As for sweets, creme brulee is good and they burn it right on the table so it is also a bit of a show. Now tiramisu is completely wrong, it has cake instead of ladyfingers and tastes A LOT like cinnamon when it should not have any cinnamon at all.  Finally, they bring the bill while some are still eating but then they take forever to pick it up. Also, I paid in cash once and was given the change in $1 bills, ten of them. Please pay your waiters a decent salary so that they do not need to use these tactics for higher tips.
